    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's just a sentiment, isn't it? logically though, if the universe is indifferent and everything eventually ends in nothingness, the net value of existing is zero. if existence and non-existence both result in zero, then choosing to end it isn't a \"wrong\" choice, it's just a neutral one. isn't that just basic math?",
